I've eaten at Hola Cafe since it opened it's door. This is a great place to eat. The Owner and Family are wonderful. They used to make their own chips and Salsa fresh! It's still wonderful atmosphere. You need mask to enter, but once you order, your ok. They are painting now, it's gone from looking like a Mexican clay with decorations to all white. They had an outdoor patio with tables and chairs. I hope those come back! It's across the Street from a City park, it's located on Main Street, the City is redoing pipes under the roads at East 1 st Street and Main, so it is a big mess!! The have a few different Beers, I'm not sure if the still serve their Frozen Margarita's, but they were good. The food prices have gone up as time has gone by. But it's still reasonable and the quality is good too. They have 2 TV's, they have added Delivery now, so it's doubled in business! It runs anywhere from $3.00 and up per person. For a great place with friendly staff, and food that they take Pride in, Hola Cafe has really earned itself a beautiful place to eat. No Braille menu, No Large print menu's but Waitstaff know Menu well. They don't mind substituting items either. Great folks who have joined our Community and employment opportunities is a great addition to SPRINGFIELD COMMUNITY, in Downtown.😁💝
